    "skin surface or above the muscle are termed as surface EMG 13.",
    "Professionals use the EMG signals to diagnose muscular disease and enhance the societal recognition of individuals affected by social disabilities.",
    "These EMG signals are employed to control computers, robotic devices, and prosthetics 14.",
    "Moreover, these EMG signals are utilized while designing efficient Human-Computer Interface (HCI) techniques for rehabilitation devices.Later, reliable validations are suggested to validate the day-to-day physical activities of disabled individuals to monitor their medical conditions and to suggest better treatment for the patients 15,16.",
    "Continuous monitoring of human motions and postures is termed as a helpful element in the human motion intention and behavior validation models 17,18."
